<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-07-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-07-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="200" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d200">
                        <head>No. 196.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">L.
                                    West</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-07-03"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 3, 1886</date>.
                                [Received July 6.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 2d, reporting the detention of the American
                            schooner City Point, of Portland, Me., by the authorities of Shelburne,
                            Nova Scotia.</p>
                        <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                        <closer><signed>L. S. SACKVILLE WEST.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>